Package info.orestes.rest.conversion

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Context  
    ReadableContext
    A readable Context that can be used by a ConverterFormat to reads and crates a processable format
    WritableContext
    A writable Context that can be used by a ConverterFormat to writes a processed format
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConversionHandler
    The ConversionHandler use the ConverterService to process the request and response entity which are returned by Request.getEntity() and set by Response.setEntity(Object).
    Converter<T,F>
    A Converter converts a specific java type T between an format and the java object.
    ConverterFormat<F>
    A ConverterFormat is used to read a format from a ReadableContext and write a format to a WritableContext.
    ConverterService
    This ConverterService is used by the ConversionHandler to transform request arguments and request entities between java types and representations as well as for response entities.
    MediaType
    This class represents a HTTP media type which can be prioritized by a quality factor q
    SimpleContext
    Created by Malte on 04.08.2014.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Accept
    Converters that are annotated with this annotation indicates that they can handle the specified MediaTypes representation of an entity
